GamePage already computes `accuracy` from hits/misses and passes it to GameHud as a prop, but GameHud's prop list doesn't include it and it never renders. Display live accuracy in the HUD so players can track shot quality mid-round without waiting for game over.

GameOverOverlay has a full `bestScore` prop, `isNewBestScore` flag, and "New Best" badge already written â€” but GamePage never passes `bestScore`. Derive the player's previous best score from `roundHistory` in App.jsx and thread it through to make the badge actually fire.

PowerupTray shows "Unlock: streak N" but gives no sense of progress toward the next charge. Each powerup has `awardEvery` and `streak` is available in GamePage â€” add a small fill bar per powerup slot showing `streak % awardEvery` hits completed so players feel the build-up.

GamePage passes `modeLabel`, `playerRankLabel`, `playerRankMmr`, `playerRankToNextTier`, and `allowsRankProgression` to GameHud but none of those props appear in GameHud's destructuring or JSX. At minimum, render the current mode label during play so the player knows what mode they are in mid-round.

`getProfileAvatarStyle` receives `seedText` but ignores it and always returns the same red gradient, so every player with no profile image looks identical. Hash the username characters to a hue angle and generate a distinct HSL gradient per player.

HistoryPage is a raw table with no aggregation â€” there is no summary of totals anywhere on the page. Add a compact stat strip above the table showing total rounds, cumulative XP earned, total coins earned, and all-time best score derived from the same `roundHistory` array already passed in.

LeaderboardPage calls `buildPlayerLeaderboardStats(rankedHistory)` â€” ranked rounds only â€” for the player's bestScore, bestStreak, and accuracy in their leaderboard row, while mock players carry all-time stats. Pass the full `roundHistory` instead so the player row is built on the same basis as everyone else.

GameOverOverlay computes `levelXpAfterRound` and `levelXpCap` and shows them as a text string ("X/Y XP"), but ProfilePage already has a visual level progress bar with the same two values. Replace the text-only level progress row in the game-over rewards section with a bar using those same computed values.

"Play Again" returns to ReadyOverlay which restarts the mode carousel, forcing the player to navigate back to their mode before hitting Start. Add a secondary "Rematch" action on GameOverOverlay that skips the carousel and immediately starts a countdown with the same `roundMode` that just ended.

PlayerHoverCard shows Coin Vault, XP Level, and Accuracy but no round count, so there is no way to judge whether a player's accuracy is based on 3 rounds or 300. Add a Rounds Played row using the existing data already present on leaderboard player objects and passed from `roundHistory` for the current player.
